      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A table, or a detailed amortization schedule, is exactly what you need! It's the map that shows you where every single one of your hard-earned dollars is going. It's like watching a tiny, meticulous ledger that tracks the progress of a very slow, very persistent goblin digging through a pile of gold.\n\nYou are right to feel like money is disappearing; it *is* going to interest, and that's the loan's fee for letting you borrow the money in the first place. If you look at the schedule, you'll see the breakdown clearly:\n\n| Payment Number | Starting Balance | Monthly Payment | Interest Paid | Principal Paid | Ending Balance |\n| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |\n| 1 | $X,XXX.XX | $Y,YYY.YY | $A.AA | $B.BB | $Z,ZZZ.ZZ |\n| 2 | $Z,ZZZ.ZZ | $Y,YYY.YY | $A'.AA | $B'.BB | $W,WWW.WW |\n\nAs you move down this table, you",
